title: Opening
---
VEX: A moment that happened fifteen years ago feels like it was yesterday.
VEX: Lashes fluttered towards the neck of her gifted spruce violin. Her fingers danced across strings with methodic passion.
VEX: She played notes of Heaven from her shoulder, enchanting the nation as much as a young prodigy could.
VEX: My hands shook across piano keys while I struggled to keep up. I was confused. I didn't know yet what I wanted from life.
VEX: All I knew in that instance was that I wanted her.
<<jump Dialogue1>>
